  "title": "Conflicting Staging Geometry",
  "concept": "A performer's position that gives cameras a clean shot can block sightlines for seats, and a position that works for the room can break the frame for screens—the staging geometry that solves one problem creates the other.",
  "interactiveId": "ca3b6d04-4fa1-4dd7-838c-13bc8f1862dd",
  "sourcePieceId": "2b79eccc-dce1-480d-9fd4-ae958883d6ef",
  "publishedAt": 1778767725893,
  "voiceScore": 88,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Conflicting Staging Geometry</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --gold: #c9a227;\n    --teal: #1a6b62;\n    --red: #c44536;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--teal);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 8ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .stage-container {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .stage-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 12px;\n  }\n  .stage-view {\n    width: 100%;\n    max-width: 420px;\n    height: 280px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    position: relative;\n    background: var(--line);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n  }\n  .stage-circle {\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 140px;\n    height: 140px;\n    border: 2px solid var(--muted);\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    top: 50%;\n    left: 50%;\n    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);\n  }\n  .performer {\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 24px;\n    height: 24px;\n    background: var(--gold);\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    border: 2px solid var(--fg);\n    transition: all 250ms ease-out;\n    z-index: 10;\n  }\n  .camera-icon {\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 32px;\n    height: 32px;\n    background: var(--teal);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    font-size: 0.65rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: #fff;\n  }\n  .camera-icon.bad {\n    background: var(--red);\n    opacity: 0.7;\n  }\n  .seat-section {\n    position: absolute;\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 3px;\n  }\n  .seat-section.top {\n    top: 8px;\n    left: 50%;\n    transform: translateX(-50%);\n  }\n  .seat-section.bottom {\n    bottom: 8px;\n    left: 50%;\n    transform: translateX(-50%);\n  }\n  .seat-section.left {\n    left: 8px;\n    top: 50%;\n    transform: translateY(-50%);\n    flex-direction: column;\n  }\n  .seat-section.right {\n    right: 8px;\n    top: 50%;\n    transform: translateY(-50%);\n    flex-direction: column;\n  }\n  .seat {\n    width: 10px;\n    height: 10px;\n    background: var(--teal);\n    border-radius: 2px;\n    transition: background 250ms ease-out, opacity 250ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .seat.blocked {\n    background: var(--red);\n    opacity: 0.7;\n  }\n  .sightline {\n    position: absolute;\n    height: 1px;\n    background: var(--red);\n    opacity: 0.3;\n    transform-origin: left center;\n    pointer-events: none;\n  }\n  .camera-frame {\n    position: absolute;\n    border: 2px dashed var(--teal);\n    pointer-events: none;\n    transition: all 250ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .camera-frame.bad {\n    border-color: var(--red);\n  }\n  .status-grid {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n    gap: 16px;\n    margin-top: 20px;\n  }\n  .status-box {\n    padding: 12px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n  }\n  .status-box h4 {\n    margin: 0 0 6px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .status-value {\n    font-size: 1.1rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .status-value.good { color: var(--teal); }\n  .status-value.bad { color: var(--red); }\n  .status-detail {\n    margin-top: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .stage-view {\n      height: 240px;\n    }\n    .status-grid {\n      grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to move the performer around the stage</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Watch how the position that helps cameras blocks seats, and the position that helps seats breaks the camera frame.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"position\">Position:</label>\n  <input id=\"position\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"360\" value=\"0\" step=\"1\" aria-describedby=\"position-out\">\n  <output id=\"position-out\" for=\"position\">Center</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"stage-container\">\n  <div class=\"stage-label\">Stage (top-down view)</div>\n  <div class=\"stage-view\" id=\"stage\">\n    <div class=\"stage-circle\"></div>\n    <div class=\"performer\" id=\"performer\"></div>\n    <div class=\"camera-icon\" id=\"camera\" style=\"top: 12px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);\">CAM</div>\n    <div class=\"camera-frame\" id=\"frame\"></div>\n    <div class=\"seat-section top\" id=\"seats-top\"></div>\n    <div class=\"seat-section bottom\" id=\"seats-bottom\"></div>\n    <div class=\"seat-section left\" id=\"seats-left\"></div>\n    <div class=\"seat-section right\" id=\"seats-right\"></div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"status-grid\">\n    <div class=\"status-box\">\n      <h4>Camera</h4>\n      <div class=\"status-value\" id=\"camera-status\">Clean shot</div>\n      <div class=\"status-detail\" id=\"camera-detail\">Performer in frame, facing forward</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"status-box\">\n      <h4>Seats</h4>\n      <div class=\"status-value\" id=\"seats-status\">12 clear</div>\n      <div class=\"status-detail\" id=\"seats-detail\">All sightlines open</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">The camera sits at the top, facing down. Seats surround the stage. Moving the performer to face the camera blocks the seats behind them. Moving the performer to circle the stage gives the camera their back or side.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('position');\n    var positionOut = document.getElementById('position-out');\n    var performer = document.getElementById('performer');\n    var camera = document.getElementById('camera');\n    var frame = document.getElementById('frame');\n    var cameraStatus = document.getElementById('camera-status');\n    var cameraDetail = document.getElementById('camera-detail');\n    var seatsStatus = document.getElementById('seats-status');\n    var seatsDetail = document.getElementById('seats-detail');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n    var stage = document.getElementById('stage');\n\n    var seatsTop = document.getElementById('seats-top');\n    var seatsBottom = document.getElementById('seats-bottom');\n    var seatsLeft = document.getElementById('seats-left');\n    var seatsRight = document.getElementById('seats-right');\n\n    var seatElements = [];\n\n    // Build 12 seat markers (3 per side)\n    function buildSeats(container, count) {\n      var arr = [];\n      for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {\n        var seat = document.createElement('div');\n        seat.className = 'seat';\n        container.appendChild(seat);\n        arr.push(seat);\n      }\n      return arr;\n    }\n\n    var seatsTopArr = buildSeats(seatsTop, 3);\n    var seatsBottomArr = buildSeats(seatsBottom, 3);\n    var seatsLeftArr = buildSeats(seatsLeft, 3);\n    var seatsRightArr = buildSeats(seatsRight, 3);\n    seatElements = seatsTopArr.concat(seatsBottomArr, seatsLeftArr, seatsRightArr);\n\n    function update() {\n      var angle = +slider.value;\n      var rad = (angle * Math.PI) / 180;\n\n      // Performer moves in a circle (radius 70px from stage center)\n      var radius = 70;\n      var centerX = stage.offsetWidth / 2;\n      var centerY = stage.offsetHeight / 2;\n      var px = centerX + radius * Math.cos(rad);\n      var py = centerY + radius * Math.sin(rad);\n\n      performer.style.left = px + 'px';\n      performer.style.top = py + 'px';\n      performer.style.transform = 'translate(-50%, -50%)';\n\n      // Position label\n      if (angle < 30 || angle > 330) {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Facing camera';\n      } else if (angle >= 30 && angle < 90) {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Right side';\n      } else if (angle >= 90 && angle < 150) {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Back to camera';\n      } else if (angle >= 150 && angle < 210) {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Left side';\n      } else if (angle >= 210 && angle < 270) {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Circling';\n      } else {\n        positionOut.textContent = 'Returning';\n      }\n\n      // Camera quality:\n      // Camera is at top (angle 0 is facing camera directly).\n      // Clean shot when performer faces camera (angle near 0 or 360).\n      // Bad shot when performer's back is to camera (angle near 180) or side (90/270).\n      var facingCamera = Math.abs(Math.cos(rad)); // 1 when facing, 0 when perpendicular\n      var cameraGood = facingCamera > 0.7; // Tight threshold: must be nearly facing\n\n      if (cameraGood) {\n        camera.classList.remove('bad');\n        cameraStatus.textContent = 'Clean shot';\n        cameraStatus.className = 'status-value good';\n        cameraDetail.textContent = 'Performer in frame, facing forward';\n        frame.style.display = 'block';\n        frame.classList.remove('bad');\n        // Draw frame around performer (tight box)\n        frame.style.left = (px - 40) + 'px';\n        frame.style.top = (py - 40) + 'px';\n        frame.style.width = '80px';\n        frame.style.height = '80px';\n      } else {\n        camera.classList.add('bad');\n        cameraStatus.textContent = 'Bad angle';\n        cameraStatus.className = 'status-value bad';\n        if (facingCamera < 0.3) {\n          cameraDetail.textContent = 'Performer\\'s back or side to camera';\n        } else {\n          cameraDetail.textContent = 'Performer partially turned away';\n        }\n        frame.style.display = 'block';\n        frame.classList.add('bad');\n        frame.style.left = (px - 40) + 'px';\n        frame.style.top = (py - 40) + 'px';\n        frame.style.width = '80px';\n        frame.style.height = '80px';\n      }\n\n      // Seats: blocked when performer is between them and center stage.\n      // Seats at top are blocked when performer is in top half (angle 270-90).\n      // Seats at bottom are blocked when performer is in bottom half (90-270).\n      // Seats at left are blocked when performer is in left half (180-360/0).\n      // Seats at right are blocked when performer is in right half (0-180).\n      var blockedCount = 0;\n\n      // Top seats (angle 315-45 blocked)\n      if ((angle >= 315 || angle <= 45)) {\n        seatsTopArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.add('blocked'); });\n        blockedCount += 3;\n      } else {\n        seatsTopArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.remove('blocked'); });\n      }\n\n      // Bottom seats (angle 135-225 blocked)\n      if (angle >= 135 && angle <= 225) {\n        seatsBottomArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.add('blocked'); });\n        blockedCount += 3;\n      } else {\n        seatsBottomArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.remove('blocked'); });\n      }\n\n      // Left seats (angle 225-315 blocked)\n      if (angle >= 225 && angle <= 315) {\n        seatsLeftArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.add('blocked'); });\n        blockedCount += 3;\n      } else {\n        seatsLeftArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.remove('blocked'); });\n      }\n\n      // Right seats (angle 45-135 blocked)\n      if (angle >= 45 && angle <= 135) {\n        seatsRightArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.add('blocked'); });\n        blockedCount += 3;\n      } else {\n        seatsRightArr.forEach(function(s) { s.classList.remove('blocked'); });\n      }\n\n      var clearCount = 12 - blockedCount;\n      if (blockedCount === 0) {\n        seatsStatus.textContent = '12 clear';\n        seatsStatus.className = 'status-value good';\n        seatsDetail.textContent = 'All sightlines open';\n      } else {\n        seatsStatus.textContent = clearCount + ' clear';\n        seatsStatus.className = 'status-value bad';\n        seatsDetail.textContent = blockedCount + ' seat' + (blockedCount > 1 ? 's' : '') + ' see performer\\'s back';\n      }\n\n      // Caption\n      if (cameraGood && blockedCount === 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Facing the camera AND giving every seat a clear view is impossible—this position is a rare compromise, not a solution.';\n      } else if (cameraGood && blockedCount > 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'The position that gives the camera a clean shot puts the performer\\'s back to the seats behind them. The geometry that solves one problem creates the other.';\n      } else if (!cameraGood && blockedCount === 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Circling the stage opens sightlines for every seat, but the camera loses the frame—it sees the performer\\'s side or back, not their face.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'Both audiences struggle. The performer is turned away from the camera AND blocking seats. Moving them helps one side and hurts the other.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
